# LEGAL‑CALCULUS USER WORKFLOW

```
             THE 5‑STEP LOOP (ALWAYS THE SAME)
```

1. OPEN REPO
    - User opens GitHub
    - User selects the file or artifact
    - Copilot cannot access the repo
2. BRING CONTENT INTO COPILOT
    - Copy/paste text from GitHub
    - Or upload the file
    - This is the ONLY way Copilot sees repo content
3. THINK WITH COPILOT PRO
    - Analyze
    - Rewrite
    - Structure
    - Build modules
    - Stress‑test arguments
    - Blueprint AI workflows
    (Copilot = thinking engine)
4. USER DECIDES
    - Review output
    - Revise
    - Approve or reject
    (Human = final authority)
5. COMMIT TO GITHUB
    - Paste improved content back into repo
    - Commit changes
    - Repo becomes the living archive

